# ============================================================
# GOVERNANCE CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: governance
scope: governance.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for governance.

## policy_rules
Governance policy constrains:
- who may decide
- who may review
- who may oversee or escalate
- what governance detail may be disclosed
- when governance paths must be denied or escalated

## required_behavior
- decision scope must be explicit
- review/oversight scope must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- public governance summary
- operator-scoped detail
- reviewer/oversight detail
- historical governance detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow governance action only for valid role scope
- allow disclosure only for allowed actors
- deny hidden role merging between decision and review
- deny disclosure beyond allowed scope

## escalation_rules
If governance context,
role separation,
oversight scope,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the governance path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- decision policy is explicit
- oversight policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- denial behavior is explicit
